    "body": "## Problem\r\n'vim.secure.trust({action='allow',path=...})' throws an error \"path is not valid when action is allow\" this - as discussed in #37423 -  makes the API inconsistent as the path parameter is available in both the 'deny' and 'remove' actions. It also makes automation harder as discussed in #27627.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n- removed the assertion \r\n```lua\r\nif action == 'allow' then\r\n    assert(not path, '\"path\" is not valid when action is \"allow\"')\r\nend\r\n```\r\n- added test: 'trust then deny then remove a file using path'\r\n- changed the documentation in editing.txt\r\n\r\nThis is my first contributions, so ill be more than happy for any feedback or work i can do! thanks for your time.",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-26T02:55:06Z",
